  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to quantitate electrical dyssynchrony in heart failure (HF)
      patients with a narrow QRS complexes (≤ 130 ms) using the ECG Belt. This is a pilot study
      that is designed to provide data that can be used in designing and implementing a prospective
      study of cardiac resynchronization therapy (CRT) in narrow QRS patients selected and
      optimized using the ECG Belt.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
